Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20logistics%20of%20terraforming%20and%20building%20a%20self-sustaining%20city%20on%20Mars%20%E2%80%94%20which%20he%20estimates%20could%20be%20done%20in%2020%20to%2030%20years.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20we'll%20launch%20the%20first%20Starship%20to%20Mars%20in%20less%20than%20three%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhen%20asked%20whether%20he'd%20like%20to%20die%20on%20Mars%2C%20Musk%20responded%2C%20%26quot%3BSure%2C%20why%20not%20die%20on%20Mars.%20I%20just%20don't%20want%20to%20die%20on%20impact.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHis%20AI%20company%2C%20xAI%2C%20bringing%20its%20chatbot%20Grok%20to%20Tesla.%20Musk%20said%20users%20will%20be%20able%20to%20ask%20it%20to%20go%20pick%20up%20a%20friend%20or%20groceries.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHis%20optimism%20about%20Optimus%20humanoid%20robots%2C%20which%20he%20anticipates%20will%20come%20to%20Tesla%20within%20the%20next%20year%20or%20two.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMusk's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-favorite-podcasts-the-explorers-hardcore-history-2024-6%23%3A~%3Atext%3DDan%2520Carlin%2527s%2520%2522Hardcore%2520History%2522%2520podcast%2Cfavorites%2520in%2520another%2520medium%253A%2520audiobooks.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epodcast%20recommendations%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20included%20%26quot%3BThe%20Age%20of%20Napoleon%26quot%3B%20and%20Dan%20Carlin's%20%26quot%3BHardcore%20History.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESpaceX's%20plans%20to%20take%20a%20lens%20from%20a%20ground%20telescope%20and%20put%20it%20in%20space.%20Musk%20said%20combining%20the%20ground%20lens%20with%20more%20advanced%20electronics%20would%20%26quot%3Bprobably%20be%20roughly%2010%20times%20the%20resolution%20of%20Hubble.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EStarship's%203D%20metal%20printed%20engine%20parts%20and%20the%20multiple%20prior%20iterations%20Musk%20went%20through%20before%20settling%20on%20the%20final%20rocket%20design.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20also%20answered%20random%20questions%20from%20the%20chat%2C%20like%20what%20he's%20drinking%20(Diet%20Coke)%20and%20whether%20Tesla%20plans%20to%20launch%20a%20phone%20(no).%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20ways%2C%20his%20game%20sessions%20feel%20like%20an%20extended%20edition%20of%20his%20speeches%20during%20a%20Tesla%20earnings%20call%20or%20while%20onstage%20at%20a%20company%20event%20or%20panel%20interview.%20But%20it's%20rare%20to%20see%20a%20CEO%20stream%20and%20talk%20for%20hours%20about%20such%20a%20range%20of%20topics%2C%20free%20from%20PR%20handlers%2C%20and%20for%20people%20following%20Musk%2C%20they%20might%20just%20hear%20something%20new%20between%20dungeon%20fights%20and%20quests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20the%20first%20alternative%20account%20Musk%20has%20been%20found%20using.%20He%20appeared%20to%20have%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-alternative-account-tweeting-as-2-year-old-son-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EX%20account%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20he%20would%20tweet%20as%20his%20now-four-year-old%20son%20X%20%C3%86%20A-12.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-gamer-streams-riff-on-tesla-spacex-neuralink-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718703782000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bc89446fcb546d2d4b72db%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-gamer-streams-riff-on-tesla-spacex-neuralink-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Elon%20Musk%20has%20been%20streaming%20video%20games%20on%20X%20while%20talking%20about%20future%20plans%20with%20Tesla%2C%20SpaceX%2C%20Neuralink%2C%20and%20more.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Jaures%20Yip)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-gamer-streams-riff-on-tesla-spacex-neuralink-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20retirement%20Catch-22%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22old%20worker%20worries%20about%20his%20job%20prospects%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66673ee7e0790490181778c1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAge%20discrimination%20undermines%20Larry%20Fink's%20%26quot%3Bsolution%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20retirement%20crisis.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20LinkedIn%3B%20Chelsea%20Jia%20Feng%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAmerica%20is%20running%20headlong%20into%20a%20big%20problem%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomer-greed-ruined-economy-gen-z-millennials-labor-shortage-inflation-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBoomers%20are%20getting%20older%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20the%20coming%20years%2C%20the%20retirement-age%20population%20will%20balloon%20to%20its%20largest%20size%20yet%2C%20drawing%20down%20Social%20Security%20funds%2C%20overwhelming%20retirement%20homes%2C%20and%20leaving%20a%20labor%20shortage%20in%20its%20wake.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELarry%20Fink%2C%20the%2071-year-old%20CEO%20of%20the%20asset-management%20behemoth%20BlackRock%2C%20offered%20a%20two-part%20solution%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-crisis-social-security-savings-401k-genz-investing-blackrock-fink-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elooming%20retirement%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkey-takeaways-blackrock-ceo-larry-finks-letter-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannual%20March%20letter%20to%20shareholders%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20order%20to%20avoid%20economic%20catastrophe%2C%20he%20argued%2C%20people%20should%20save%20more%20money%20and%20work%20longer.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20if%20the%20government%20and%20the%20private%20sector%20treated%2060-plus%20year-olds%20as%20late-career%20workers%20with%20much%20to%20offer%20rather%20than%20people%20who%20should%20retire%3F%26quot%3B%20Fink%20wrote.%20The%20current%20Social%20Security%20retirement%20age%20is%2067%2C%20but%20most%20Americans%20depart%20the%20workforce%20earlier%20than%20that.%20If%20more%20people%20kept%20working%20into%20their%20late%2060s%20and%2070s%2C%20the%20impending%20crisis%20would%20soften.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20ways%2C%20Fink's%20solution%20sounds%20nice%20and%20even%20sensible%20%E2%80%94%20many%20able-bodied%2C%20energetic%2070-year-olds%20are%20happy%20to%20stay%20employed%20and%20contribute%20to%20the%20economy%2C%20so%20why%20not%20encourage%20more%20people%20to%20do%20the%20same%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20is%20that%20his%20plan%20overlooks%20a%20few%20key%20realities.%20For%20one%2C%20many%20older%20people%20cannot%20work%20because%20of%20a%20disability%20or%20because%20they%20need%20to%20care%20for%20someone%20else%20with%20a%20disability.%20The%20second%20is%20that%20those%20who%20are%20willing%20and%20able%20to%20work%20are%20often%20unwanted.%20Despite%20a%20legal%20ban%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffired-78-year-old-receptionist-wins-age-discrimination-case-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ediscriminating%20against%20people%2040%20and%20older%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%20it's%20still%20common.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20making%20it%20easier%20for%20Americans%20to%20save%20for%20retirement%20and%20work%20as%20long%20(or%20as%20short)%20as%20they%20want%2C%20Fink%20is%20setting%20up%20a%20catch-22%3A%20The%20economy%20needs%20aging%20Americans%20to%20work%20longer%2C%20but%20many%20companies%20simply%20don't%20want%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EDown%20in%20Texas%2C%20Daniel%20Ross%20has%20been%20busy.%20As%20a%20founding%20partner%20of%20Ross%20Scalise%20Employment%20Lawyers%2C%20an%20Austin%20firm%20that%20represents%20people%20who%20have%20experienced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshocked-when-recruiter-said-too-old-tech-job-ageism-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eage%20discrimination%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20this%20isn't%20necessarily%20a%20good%20thing.%20Over%20the%20past%20five%20years%2C%20he%20said%20he's%20noticed%20an%20increase%20in%20age-discrimination%20cases%2C%20especially%20those%20alleging%20wrongful%20discharge.%20%26quot%3BHere%20in%20Austin%2C%20we%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20tech%20jobs%20and%20tech%20companies%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20want%20to%20look%20younger.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20a%20Society%20for%20Human%20Resources%20Management%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.shrm.org%2Fabout%2Fpress-room%2Fnew-shrm-research-details-age-discrimination-workplace%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%20%3C%2Fa%3Efound%20that%2030%25%20of%20workers%20felt%20discriminated%20against%20because%20of%20their%20age%20at%20some%20point%20in%20their%20careers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20absolutely%20isn't%20good%20when%20we%20are%20in%20a%20moment%20in%20time%20where%20we%20still%20have%20so%20many%20more%20jobs%20to%20fill%20and%20people%20who%20are%20trained%20to%20fill%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Emily%20Dickens%2C%20SHRM's%20head%20of%20government%20affairs%2C%20said%20about%20the%20survey%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20US%20Chamber%20of%20Commerce%2C%20there%20are%208.5%20million%20open%20jobs%20in%20the%20US%20and%20only%206.5%20million%20unemployed%20people%20looking%20for%20work.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaby-boomer-retirement-surge-spark-forever-labor-shortage-jobs-workers-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshortages%20span%20several%20industries%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20healthcare%2C%20hospitality%2C%20and%20business%20services%20such%20as%20accounting%20topping%20the%20list%20for%20the%20most%20unfilled%20positions.%20In%20the%20Texas%20tech%20scene%2C%20job%20openings%20are%20on%20the%20rise.%20But%20despite%20the%20shortages%2C%20many%20companies%20are%20reluctant%20to%20fill%20their%20open%20roles%20with%20older%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPatrick%20Button%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20economics%20at%20Tulane%20University%2C%20has%20done%20extensive%20work%20on%20employment%20discrimination%2C%20mostly%20through%20what's%20known%20as%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20correspondence%20field%20experiments.%20These%20studies%20involve%20creating%20fictional%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20that%20vary%20in%20a%20few%20ways%20and%20using%20them%20to%20apply%20for%20job%20openings.%20The%20number%20of%20callbacks%20that%20each%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20receives%20indicates%20the%20employer%20response%20to%20that%20type%20of%20worker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.journals.uchicago.edu%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1086%2F701029%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOne%20of%20Button's%20studies%20looked%20at%20%26quot%3Bbridge%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cu%3E%2C%3C%2Fu%3E%26quot%3B%20part-time%20jobs%20in%20administration%20or%20retail%20that%20many%20people%20use%20to%20ease%20into%20retirement%20and%20cushion%20their%20finances.%20%26quot%3BThe%20ability%20to%20get%20these%20sorts%20of%20jobs%20is%20one%20mechanism%20that%20older%20people%20use%20to%20work%20longer%20and%20then%20provide%20better%20security%20for%20themselves%20in%20retirement%2C%26quot%3B%20Button%20said.%20He%20and%20his%20coauthors%20sent%20out%2040%2C000%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20they%20wrote%20to%20represent%20different%20age%20groups%3A%20younger%20workers%20between%2029%20and%2031%2C%20middle-aged%20workers%20between%2049%20and%2051%2C%20and%20older%20workers%20between%2064%20and%2066.%20They%20applied%20to%20listings%20for%20administrative%2C%20retail%20sales%2C%20security%2C%20and%20janitorial%20positions%20%E2%80%94%20all%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapplied-hundreds-jobs-struggling-get-hired-bridge-job-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etypical%20bridge%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20attract%20applicants%20from%20every%20demographic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20women%2C%20they%20discovered%20a%203%20percentage-point%20drop%20in%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20responses%20around%20age%2050%20with%20a%20significant%20decline%20around%2065.%20For%20men%2C%20the%20decline%20appeared%20at%20age%2065.%20The%20results%20were%20clear%3A%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20significant%20amount%20of%20age%20discrimination%20in%20the%20ability%20to%20take%20these%20jobs%2C%20particularly%20against%20older%20women%2C%26quot%3B%20Button%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20studies%20have%20found%20a%20similar%20pattern%3A%20A%202024%20survey%20of%201%2C000%20hiring%20managers%20conducted%20by%20ResumeBuilder.com%2C%20a%20website%20that%20helps%20people%20write%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%2C%20found%20that%20more%20than%20one-third%20of%20respondents%20admitted%20to%20a%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-managers-biased-against-gen-z-older-workers-survey-says-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20bias%20against%20candidates%20older%20than%2060%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Gen%20Z%20candidates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20in%20a%20situation%20where%20we've%20got%20one%20group%20of%20people%20who%20are%20apparently%20only%20hiring%20their%20own%20age%20group%2C%20because%20they%20seem%20to%20be%20biased%20against%20those%20younger%20than%20them%20and%20older%20than%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Stacie%20Haller%2C%20a%20chief%20career%20advisor%20at%20ResumeBuilder.com%2C%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20companies%20have%20recently%20come%20under%20fire%20for%20explicit%20age%20bias.%20A%202018%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffeatures.propublica.org%2Fibm%2Fibm-age-discrimination-american-workers%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EProPublica%20and%20Mother%20Jones%20investigation%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20IBM%20had%20an%20express%2C%20top-down%20program%20in%20place%20from%202013%20until%202018%20to%20fire%20workers%20over%2040%20and%20replace%20them%20with%20workers%20under%2040.%20The%20Equal%20Employment%20Opportunity%20Commission%20found%20that%20there%20was%20%26quot%3Breasonable%20cause%26quot%3B%20to%20believe%20that%20IBM%20discriminated%20against%20certain%20employees%20based%20on%20their%20ages.%20The%20case%20is%20ongoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20the%20pharmaceutical%20company%20Lilly%20was%20ordered%20by%20the%20EEOC%20to%20pay%20a%20%242.4%20million%20fine%20for%20a%20program%20it%20operated%20between%202017%20and%202021%20to%20attract%20%26quot%3Bearly%20career%26quot%3B%20salespeople%2C%20which%20included%20incentives%20for%20managers%20to%20hire%20people%20under%2040.%20The%20same%20year%2C%20Scripps%20Medical%20Clinic%20in%20San%20Diego%20was%20ordered%20to%20pay%20%246.9%20million%20for%20setting%20a%20mandatory%20retirement%20age%20for%20physicians%20of%2070%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20doctors'%20interest%20or%20abilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20often%2C%20though%2C%20the%20discrimination%20is%20less%20explicit.%20Ross%2C%20the%20age-discrimination%20lawyer%2C%20said%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-can-older-workers-prove-ageism-and-age-bias-in-hiring-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20of%20his%20cases%20involve%20circumstantial%20evidence.%3C%2Fa%3E%20He%20told%20me%20that%20people%20who%20would%20never%20dream%20of%20making%20remarks%20about%20race%2C%20gender%2C%20or%20religion%20will%20casually%20joke%20about%20old%20people%2C%20ask%20people%20when%20they%20are%20retiring%2C%20or%20otherwise%20contribute%20to%20making%20an%20older%20colleague%20feel%20unwelcome.%20Often%2C%20he%20said%2C%20this%20kind%20of%20circumstantial%20evidence%20helps%20him%20build%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAge%20discrimination%20happens%20for%20a%20host%20of%20reasons.%20We%20live%20in%20a%20youth-obsessed%20culture%2C%20and%20gray%20hair%20doesn't%20reflect%20corporate%20branding.%20Employers%20may%20assume%20that%20older%20workers%20have%20health%20problems%20and%20so%20might%20require%20more%20time%20off%20or%20that%20they're%20out%20of%20touch%20with%20rapidly%20changing%20technology.%20Some%20managers%20don't%20know%20how%20to%20talk%20to%20their%20older%20reports.%20And%20some%20older%20workers%20have%20heard%20all%20the%20corporate%20buzzwords%20and%20blather%20before%2C%20so%20they%20don't%20buy%20into%20management's%20sloganeering%2C%20rendering%20them%20%26quot%3Bdifficult.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCompanies%20want%20to%20create%20a%20younger%20workforce.%20And%20I%20think%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20they%20want%20to%20do%20that%20is%20so%20they%20look%20like%20a%20younger%20workforce%20to%20customers%20and%20to%20potential%20employees%20who%20are%20statistically%20going%20to%20be%20younger%20than%2040%20or%20so%2C%26quot%3B%20Ross%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20ideal%20world%2C%20older%20workers%20could%20retire%20peacefully%2C%20leaving%20the%20work%20of%20running%20the%20country's%20economic%20engine%20to%20younger%20generations%20while%20they%20enjoy%20a%20well-deserved%20break.%20But%20increasingly%2C%20retirement-aged%20Americans%20are%20stuck%20between%20a%20rock%20and%20a%20hard%20place.%20They%20can't%20retire%20when%20they%20want%20to%20because%20they%20don't%20have%20enough%20money%20saved%20up.%20But%20they%20can't%20continue%20working%2C%20either%2C%20because%20companies%20don't%20want%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELarry%20Fink%20is%20correct%20that%20most%20industrial%20countries%20have%20not%20prepared%20for%20the%20economic%20impact%20of%20an%20aging%20population.%20In%20the%20US%2C%20the%20Silent%20Generation%20and%20older%20baby%20boomers%20have%20enjoyed%20relatively%20rich%20pension%20and%20healthcare%20benefits.%20But%20for%20most%20retirees%2C%20it%20simply%20isn't%20enough.%20Fewer%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomers-not-enough-retirement-savings-gen-z-millennials-eldercare-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehalf%20of%20boomers%20have%20enough%20retirement%20savings%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-x-baby-boomers-savings-cant-afford-retirement-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone-fifth%20saying%3C%2Fa%3E%20they%20have%20none%20at%20all.%20Already%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-crisis-social-security-pensions-student-loan-debt-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretirement-age%20Americans%20are%20struggling%20to%20get%20by%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20reckoning%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpeak-boomer-scared-to-retire-not-enough-savings-social-security-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworking%20into%20their%2070s%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20order%20to%20stretch%20their%20meager%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20with%20Fink's%20assessment%20is%20that%20it%20just%20isn't%20realistic.%20He's%20asking%20people%20who%20have%20not%20yet%20retired%20to%20work%20longer%20than%20their%20elders%20did%20and%20to%20save%20even%20more%20money%2C%20without%20changing%20the%20systematic%20barriers%20to%20either.%20Sure%2C%20we've%20all%20been%20told%20that%20life%20isn't%20fair%20%E2%80%94%20usually%20by%20the%20people%20who%20hold%20all%20the%20cards%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20system%20isn't%20set%20up%20to%20help%20people%20work%20longer%20or%20save%20more%20money.%20Already%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-social-security-gen-z-millennials-uncertainty-fears-pensions-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyounger%20generations%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20panicking%20about%20how%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-millennials-need-for-retirement-savings-strategies-401k-ira-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emuch%20money%20they%20need%20to%20save%20in%20order%20to%20retire%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EF