ns.%20The%20lawsuit%20follows%20a%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%20investigation%20into%20Adobe's%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegulators%20said%20in%20the%20complaint%20that%20Adobe%20entices%20people%20to%20%26quot%3Benroll%20in%20its%20default%2C%20most%20lucrative%20subscription%20plan%20without%20clearly%20disclosing%20important%20plan%20terms.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20the%20DOJ%2C%20Adobe%20fails%20to%20tell%20users%20that%20when%20they%20sign%20up%20for%20an%20annual%20plan%20that's%20charged%20monthly%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethey%20are%20agreeing%20to%20a%20year-long%20commitment%20%E2%80%94%20including%20a%20termination%20fee%20that%20could%20be%20hundreds%20of%20dollars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20disclosures%20are%20hidden%20behind%20optional%20textboxes%20and%20hyperlinks%20and%20are%20%26quot%3Bdesigned%20to%20go%20unnoticed%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20said.%20Early%20termination%20fee%20details%20only%20appear%20when%20users%20try%20to%20cancel%2C%20effectively%20trapping%20them%20in%20subscriptions%20they%20don't%20want.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThrough%20these%20practices%2C%20Adobe%20has%20violated%20federal%20laws%20designed%20to%20protect%20consumers%2C%26quot%3B%20prosecutors%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20wrote%20that%20the%20company%20has%20been%20made%20aware%20of%20government%20scrutiny%20into%20its%20subscription%20practices%20since%20June%202022%2C%20but%20continued%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20suit%20also%20names%20two%20Adobe%20executives%20as%20defendants%3A%20Maninder%20Sawhney%2C%20the%20senior%20vice%20president%20of%20digital%20go-to-market%20and%20sales%2C%20and%20David%20Wadhwani%2C%20the%20president%20of%20the%20digital%20media%20business.%20The%20complaint%20says%20both%20executives%20%26quot%3Bdirected%2C%20controlled%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bparticipated%26quot%3B%20in%20Adobe's%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdobe%20plans%20to%20refute%20the%20government's%20claims%20in%20court%2C%20the%20company%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20transparent%20with%20the%20terms%20and%20conditions%20of%20our%20subscription%20agreements%20and%20have%20a%20simple%20cancellation%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20Dana%20Rao%2C%20Adobe's%20general%20counsel%2C%20said%20in%20the%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdobe%20previously%20sold%20its%20popular%20products%2C%20like%20Photoshop%2C%20for%20an%20upfront%20fee.%20In%20recent%20years%2C%20it%20switched%20to%20monthly%20subscriptions%2C%20which%20investors%20prefer%20because%20revenue%20is%20easier%20to%20predict.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20nearly%20doubled%20its%20subscription%20revenue%20from%202019%20to%202023%2C%20to%20%2414.2%20billion.%20Adobe%20made%20%2419.4%20billion%20overall%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221a32713b-4691-4676-99e0-a9294f0ac399%5C%22%3ENew%20terms%20of%20service%20lead%20to%20outcry%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20comes%20on%20the%20heels%20of%20another%20serious%20concern%20artists%20and%20designers%20have%20recently%20raised%20with%20Adobe%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20month%2C%20the%20tech%20giant%20asked%20users%20to%20sign%20new%20terms%20with%20language%20that%20some%20thought%20implied%20that%20their%20content%20could%20be%20reproduced%2C%20displayed%2C%20or%20modified%20by%20Adobe%20%E2%80%94%20a%20big%20concern%20since%20Adobe%20is%20pushing%20hard%20into%20generative%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20creators%20said%20they%20quit%20the%20platform%20over%20their%20licensing%20and%20AI%20scraping%20concerns%2C%20prompting%20the%20company%20to%20clarify%20the%20new%20terms%20in%20two%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.adobe.com%2Fen%2Fpublish%2F2024%2F06%2F10%2Fupdating-adobes-terms-of-use%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblog%20posts%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20last%20two%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYour%20content%20is%20yours%20and%20will%20never%20be%20used%20to%20train%20any%20generative%20AI%20tool.%20We%20will%20make%20it%20clear%20in%20the%20license%20grant%20section%20that%20any%20license%20granted%20to%20Adobe%20to%20operate%20its%20services%20will%20not%20supersede%20your%20ownership%20rights%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20pair%20of%20Adobe%20executives%20wrote%20in%20the%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20news%20even%20frustrated%20Adobe%20employees%2C%20who%20complained%20internally%20about%20the%20company's%20poor%20communication%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadobe-employees-slam-company-over-ai-controversy-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20general%20perception%20is%3A%20Adobe%20is%20an%20evil%20company%20that%20will%20do%20whatever%20it%20takes%20to%20F%20its%20users%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20employee%20wrote%20in%20an%20internal%20Slack%20message.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20clarifications%20did%20little%20to%20calm%20some%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPretending%20that%20this%20wasn't%20intentional%20only%20makes%20Adobe%20and%20its%20employees%20look%20even%20more%20pathetic%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fsashayanshin%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20Sasha%20Yanshin%20on%20X.%20%3C%2Fa%3EYanshin%20said%20that%20he%20canceled%20his%20Adobe%20subscription%20after%20many%20years%20as%20a%20customer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadobe-sued-doj-unfair-subscription-practices-ftc-investigation-signup-cancel-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718703008000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667151f8764df161125aa0fe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadobe-sued-doj-unfair-subscription-practices-ftc-investigation-signup-cancel-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20US%20government%20sued%20Adobe%2C%20saying%20it%20violated%20consumer%20protection%20laws%20by%20hiding%20expensive%20fees%20and%20making%20it%20difficult%20to%20cancel%20subscriptions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22shubhangigoel%40insider.com%20(Shubhangi%20Goel)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadobe-sued-doj-unfair-subscription-practices-ftc-investigation-signup-cancel-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Social%20media%20isn't%20like%20cigarettes%2C%20and%20a%20warning%20label%20won't%20help%20much%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dee%20Snider%20testifies%20before%20congress%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6670ac18764df161125a9699%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22630%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDee%20Snider%20of%20Twisted%20Sister%20speaks%20to%20Congress%20in%201985.%3Cp%3EMark%20Weiss%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20surgeon%20general%20is%20pushing%20for%20a%20warning%20label%20on%20social%20media%20about%20teen%20mental%20health%20risks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20comparison%20to%20cigarette%20warnings%20is%20tempting%2C%20but%20social%20media%20might%20be%20more%20like%20explicit%20lyrics.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20hard%20to%20see%20how%20a%20warning%20label%20could%20be%20as%20effective%20as%20government%20regulation.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20Surgeon%20General%20Vivek%20Murthy%20is%20recommending%20a%20warning%20label%20on%20social%20media%20sites%20cautioning%20that%20%26quot%3Bsocial%20media%20is%20associated%20with%20significant%20mental%20health%20harms%20for%20adolescents.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20label%20would%20warn%20teens%20and%20their%20parents%20of%20the%20potential%20risk%20of%20harm%20from%20using%20social%20media.%20In%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F06%2F17%2Fopinion%2Fsocial-media-health-warning.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eop-ed%20for%20The%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Murthy%20writes%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20mental%20health%20crisis%20among%20young%20people%20is%20an%20emergency%20%E2%80%94%20and%20social%20media%20has%20emerged%20as%20an%20important%20contributor.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMurthy%20references%20the%20warning%20label%20on%20tobacco%20products%2C%20which%20is%20viewed%20as%20a%20public%20health%20success%20story%2C%20helping%20reduce%20tobacco%20use%20significantly%20since%20the%201970s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20is%20social%20media%20really%20comparable%20to%20cigarettes%3F%20And%20could%20a%20warning%20label%20actually%20make%20an%20impact%3F%20Sure%2C%20apps%20like%20TikTok%20and%20Instagram%20can%20be%20addictive%20and%20potentially%20harmful.%20However%2C%20there%20are%20a%20few%20really%20basic%20differences%20that%20I%20think%20are%20worth%20considering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%20of%20all%2C%20unlike%20social%20media%20apps%2C%20cigarettes%20are%20aimed%20at%20adults%20(yes%2C%20it%20has%20also%20been%20stealthily%20marketed%20to%20teens)%2C%20and%20they%20are%20only%20%3Cem%3Elegally%3C%2Fem%3E%20sold%20to%20adults%20(yes%2C%20obviously%20teens%20are%20getting%20their%20hands%20on%20them%20anyway).%20The%20warning%20label%20is%20for%20everyone%3A%20cigarettes%20pose%20a%20health%20risk%20to%20anyone%20who%20smokes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecondly%2C%20there's%20little%20hope%20that%20tobacco%20companies%20will%20be%20inspired%20to%20make%20cigarettes%20healthy%20%E2%80%94%20there%20is%20no%20healthy%20version%20of%20an%20American%20Spirit.%20But%20there%20%3Cem%3Eis%3C%2Fem%3E%20hope%20that%20social%20media%20could%20be%20less%20harmful.%20There%20could%20be%20all%20sorts%20of%20tweaks%20and%20changes%2C%20small%20and%20large%2C%20that%20could%20make%20social%20platforms%20safer%20for%20kids.%20Big%20Tech%20platforms%20could%20make%20these%20changes%20if%20spurred%20by%20regulation%2C%20negative%20media%20coverage%2C%20advertiser%20boycotts%2C%20or%20simply%20because%20they%20believe%20it's%20the%20right%20thing%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20of%20regulation%2C%20the%20decline%20in%20cigarette%20use%20over%20the%20last%2050%20years%20has%20also%20been%20aided%20by%20smoking%20bans%20in%20offices%2C%20planes%2C%20restaurants%2C%20bars%2C%20and%20other%20public%20places.%20These%20bans%20resulted%20from%20a%20series%20of%20state%2C%20local%2C%20and%20federal%20regulations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20the%20government's%20approach%20to%20social%20media%20regulation%20has%20been%20somewhat%20chaotic.%20A%20few%20potential%20bills%20exist%2C%20like%20the%20Kids%20Online%20Safety%20Act%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.congress.gov%2Fbill%2F118th-congress%2Fsenate-bill%2F1291%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EProtecting%20Kids%20on%20Social%20Media%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20an%20overhaul%20of%20the%20existing%20COPPA%20laws%20on%20data%20privacy%20and%20advertising%20to%20kids%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20a%20bunch%20of%20state%20attorneys%20general%20who%20have%20filed%20lawsuits%20over%20social%20media%20harms%20to%20kids%2C%20and%20individual%20states%20have%20crafted%20their%20own%20laws%2C%20like%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fsocial-media-tech-kids-new-york-82779a3040385dfc26c6ee15f490234e%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20bill%20in%20New%20York%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20would%20ban%20%26quot%3Baddictive%26quot%3B%20algorithmic%20feeds%20for%20teens.%20Meta%20has%20said%20it%20would%20welcome%20regulation%20(meaning%20regulation%20that%20it%20likes)%20and%20has%20also%20suggested%20that%20it%20would%20like%20the%20responsibility%20of%20age-gating%20and%20parental%20consent%20to%20download%20social%20apps%20be%20shifted%20over%20to%20Apple%20and%20Google's%20app%20stores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20instead%20of%20thinking%20of%20social%20media%20like%20cigarettes%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20warning%20labels%2C%20there's%20another%20analogy%20that%20might%20help%20us%20make%20more%20sense%20of%20this%20moment%3A%20the%20parental%20advisory%20stickers%20on%20music%20albums%20with%20explicit%20lyrics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESocial%20media%20is%20maybe%20closer%20to%20music%20than%20cigarettes%2C%20at%20least%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20First%20Amendment%20(there's%20a%20far%20more%20obvious%20speech%20implication%20than%20the%20right%20to%20rip%20heaters%20in%20the%20airport).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20mid-1980s%2C%20a%20group%20called%20the%20Parents%20Music%20Resource%20Center%20(PMRC)%2C%20which%20included%20a%20handful%20of%20influential%20wives%20of%20senators%20like%20Tipper%20Gore%2C%20was%20incensed%20over%20songs%20like%20Prince's%20%26quot%3BDarling%20Nikki%26quot%3B%20and%20Judas%20Priest's%20%26quot%3BEat%20Me%20Alive%26quot%3B%20and%20urged%20record%20labels%20to%20attach%20warnings%20to%20albums%20containing%20explicit%20lyrics.%20The%20pressure%20campaign%20culminated%20in%20a%20media%20spectacle%20when%20John%20Denver%2C%20Frank%20Zappa%2C%20and%20Dee%20Snider%20of%20Twisted%20Sister%20spoke%20before%20Congress%20to%20defend%20their%20art.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20no%20law%20was%20passed%20%E2%80%94%20the%20parental%20advisory%20labels%20you%20still%20see%20on%20albums%20today%20resulted%20from%20self%20regulation%20by%20the%20record%20industry%20to%20avoid%20actual%20regulation%3A%20a%20compromise%20between%20the%20Recording%20Industry%20Association%20of%20America%20and%20the%20PMRC.%20(This%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F853600%3Fmag%3Dparental-advisory-the-story-of-a-warning-label%26seq%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1999%20article%20from%20the%20journal%20Popular%20Music%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20fun%20read%20if%20you're%20interested%20in%20dividing%20deeper%20into%20the%20history%20of%20the%20warning%20labels).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20surgeon%20general%20warning%20label%20that%20pops%20up%20when%20you%20open%20Instagram%20is%20probably%20going%20to%20be%20annoying%2C%20but%20it%20can't%20really%20hurt.%20So%2C%20hey%2C%20why%20not%3F%20I'm%20not%20going%20to%20sit%20here%20and%20say%20a%20government%20effort%20to%20help%20teen%20mental%20health%20is%20bad.%20Go%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20am%20skeptical%20of%20how%20effective%20it%20will%20actually%20be%2C%20and%20how%20much%20political%20capital%20might%20be%20wasted%20on%20this%20instead%20of%20the%20hard%2C%20unfun%20work%20of%20coming%20up%20with%20regulations%20on%20social%20platforms%20that%20are%20actually%20effective.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsurgeon-general-warning-label-social-media-teen-health-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718703001000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6670ac18764df161125a9699%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsurgeon-general-warning-label-social-media-teen-health-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20warning%20label%20for%20social%20media%20can't%20hurt%2C%20but%20it%20probably%20won't%20help%20much.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22knotopoulos%40businessinsider.com%20(Katie%20Notopoulos)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsurgeon-general-warning-label-social-media-teen-health-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Blockbuster%20year%20for%20Malayalam%20films%20with%20Rs%20720%20crore%20BO%20collections%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718702871000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-111082317%2Cimgsize-61416.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Findia-business%2Fblockbuster-year-for-malayalam-films-with-rs-720-crore-bo-collections-manjummel-boys-aadujeevitham-aavesham-among-top-10-movies-in-india%2Farticleshow%2F111081963.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Ma