mandants-shadow-zone-of-interest-1236040789%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fholocaust-doc-the-commandants-shadow-zone-of-interest-1236040789%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fholocaust-doc-the-commandants-shadow-zone-of-interest-1236040789%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20In%20Numbers%3A%20Brand%20Modi%20Is%20Still%20The%20Key%20Difference%20Between%20BJP%20And%20Others%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2F9m078hlg_pm-modi-oath-third-term-ians_625x300_09_June_24.jpeg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202024%20mandate%20has%20reignited%20the%20debate%20around%20'Brand%20Modi'.%20The%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party's%20(BJP)%20inability%20to%20cross%20the%20majority%20mark%20on%20its%20own%20has%20led%20some%20analysts%20to%20claim%20the%20brand%20has%20weakened%20considerably.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20despite%20losses%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20still%20emerged%20as%20the%20single-largest%20party.%20This%20coupled%20with%20the%20fact%20that%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20has%20equalled%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru's%20record%20of%20winning%20a%20successive%20third%20term%20is%20being%20seen%20by%20many%20as%20proof%20that%20the%20strength%20of%20the%20brand%20is%20still%20intact.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20BJP%20won%20240%20seats%20in%20the%20recently%20concluded%20elections%2C%20the%20Congress%20won%2099.%20Alliance-wise%2C%20while%20the%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20(NDA)%20won%20292%20seats%20and%20around%2044%25%20votes%2C%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20got%20234%20seats%20and%20registered%20a%2041%25%20vote%20share.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20'Modi%20premium'%20or%20the%20'Modi%20factor'%20can%20be%20defined%20as%20PM%20Modi's%20ability%20to%20attract%20voters%20who%20are%20not%20among%20the%20party's%20core%20vote%20banks.%20Post-poll%20data%20released%20by%20the%20Centre%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20Developing%20Societies%20(CSDS)%20and%20some%20associated%20research%20carried%20out%20by%20this%20author%20point%20to%20some%20answers%20to%20questions%20about%20the%20popularity%20of%20this%20'brand'.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELocalised%20Elections%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20national%20level%2C%20the%20election%20this%20year%20was%20more%20localised%20than%20the%202019%20polls.%20Just%2010%25%20of%20voters%20said%20they%20considered%20the%20prime%20ministerial%20face%20as%20the%20most%20important%20factor%20while%20voting%20-%20%C2%A0down%20from%2017%25%20in%202019.%20Correspondingly%2C%20the%20share%20of%20voters%20who%20focused%20on%20their%20local%20candidates%20increased%20from%2031%25%20in%202019%20to%2036%25%20this%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20Prime%20Ministerial%20preference%2C%20while%20Narendra%20Modi%20received%2041%25%20support%2C%20Rahul%20Gandhi's%20ratings%20were%20just%20around%2027%25.%20Though%20the%20gap%20is%20still%20significant%2C%20it%20has%20narrowed%20since%202019%2C%20when%20Modi's%20ratings%20were%2047%25%20and%20Rahul's%2023%25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20multiply%20the%20leadership%20gap%20by%20the%20number%20of%20respondents%20voting%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20prime%20ministerial%20face%2C%20it%20can%20be%20said%20that%20in%20terms%20of%20vote%20share%2C%20the%20BJP's%20leadership%20advantage%20fetched%20the%20party%20and%20its%20allies%20roughly%204.1%25%20votes%20in%202019.%20This%20has%20declined%20to%20just%201.4%25%20in%202024.%20Further%2C%20in%20the%20previous%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%2C%2032%25%20of%20voters%20who%20backed%20the%20BJP%20said%20they%20would%20not%20have%20voted%20for%20it%20if%20Modi%20were%20not%20its%20prime%20ministerial%20candidate.%20The%20share%20of%20such%20voters%20has%20declined%20to%2025%25%20now%2C%20veering%20closer%20to%20the%202014%20figure%20of%2027%25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EStill%20The%20USP%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20PM%20Modi's%20popularity%20helps%20not%20just%20the%20BJP%20but%20also%20its%20allies.%20In%202014%2C%20he%20fetched%2020%25%20of%20votes%20for%20the%20BJP's%20allies%2C%2025%25%20in%202019%2C%20and%2027%25%20in%202024.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20in%202019%2C%20the%20BJP%20recorded%20a%2037.8%25%20vote%20share.%20According%20to%20this%20author's%20research%2C%2025.7%25%20of%20this%20came%20from%20its%20core%20ideological%20base%2C%20while%2012.1%25%20can%20be%20attributed%20to%20the%20'Modi%20factor'.%20This%20year%2C%20of%20the%20BJP's%2036.6%25%20vote%20share%2C%20the%20core%20base%20accounts%20for%20about%2027.4%25%20votes%20and%20the%20'Modi%20factor'%20around%209.2%25.%20This%20implies%20that%20the%20'Modi%20premium'%20has%20declined%20from%20around%2012%25%20in%202019%20to%20around%209%25%20now.%20Nonetheless%2C%20Modi%20still%20fetches%209%25%20support%20for%20the%20BJP%2C%20three%20times%20the%20difference%20between%20the%20vote%20shares%20of%20the%20NDA%20and%20the%20INDIA%20bloc.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20be%20argued%20that%20without%20Modi%2C%20the%20NDA%20would%20have%20struggled%20to%20form%20a%20government.%20He%20was%20the%20difference%20between%20the%20two%20blocs.%20The%20numbers%20below%20illustrate%20this%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%202014%2C%20the%20NDA%20bagged%20around%205.5%20crore%20votes%20based%20on%20the%20Modi%20factor.%20The%20NDA's%20lead%20over%20the%20Congress-led%20United%20Progressive%20Alliance%20(UPA)%20was%20around%208.7%20crore%20votes.%20This%20means%20the%20Modi%20factor%20accounted%20for%2063%25%20of%20NDA's%20lead.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%20the%20next%20elections%2C%20the%20NDA%20got%20around%208.5%20crore%20votes%2C%20while%20the%20NDA's%20lead%20was%2011%20crore.%20Thus%2C%20the%20Modi%20factor%20accounted%20for%2077%25%20of%20NDA's%20winning%20margin.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%20the%20latest%20round%2C%20Modi%20fetched%20the%20NDA%20around%207.1%20crore%20votes%2C%20while%20the%20NDA's%20lead%20over%20India%20was%20around%202%20crore.%20The%20Modi%20factor%20thus%20accounted%20for%20much%20more%20than%20the%20NDA's%20lead%20and%20was%20the%20key%20differentiating%20factor%20between%20it%20and%20the%20opposition%20front.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHence%2C%20the%20BJP's%20victory%20in%20240%20seats%20and%20the%20NDA's%20in%20292%20seats%20may%20have%20been%20difficult%20without%20Modi.%20Brand%20Modi%20may%20have%20aged%20-%20or%20perhaps%20peaked%20as%20well%20-%20after%2010%20years%20in%20power%2C%20but%20it's%20still%20the%20prime%20differentiator%20between%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20Congress.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Amitabh%20Tiwari%20is%20a%20political%20strategist%20and%20commentator.%20In%20his%20earlier%20avatar%2C%20he%20was%20a%20corporate%20and%20investment%20banker.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718700300000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2F9m078hlg_pm-modi-oath-third-term-ians_625x300_09_June_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fbrand-modi-is-still-the-key-difference-between-bjp-and-others-5914932%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Brand%20Modi%20may%20have%20aged%20-%20or%20perhaps%20peaked%20as%20well%20-%20after%2010%20years%20in%20power%2C%20but%20it's%20still%20the%20prime%20differentiator%20between%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20Congress.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fbrand-modi-is-still-the-key-difference-between-bjp-and-others-5914932%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fbrand-modi-is-still-the-key-difference-between-bjp-and-others-5914932%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fbrand-modi-is-still-the-key-difference-between-bjp-and-others-5914932%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Will%20audience%20accept%20Ranbir%20as%20Ram%20asks%20Sunil%20Lahri%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718700179000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-111081101%2Cimgsize-35910.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fwill-the-audience-accept-ranbir-kapoor-as-ram-in-nitesh-tiwaris-upcoming-ramayana-asks-sunil-lahri%2Farticleshow%2F111081101.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F111081101.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3ENitesh%20Tiwari%E2%80%99s%20upcoming%20film%2C%20'Ramayana'%2C%20is%20generating%20significant%20buzz%2C%20particularly%20with%20the%20casting%20of%20Ranbir%20Kapoor%20and%20Sai%20Pallavi.%20Earlier%2C%20Dipika%20Chikjlia%2C%20who%20is%20known%20for%20her%20role%20of%20Sita%20in%20Ramanand%20Sagar%E2%80%99s%20'Ramayan'%2C%20expressed%20her%20displeasure%20that%20people%20keep%20remaking%20the%20'Ramayana'.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fwill-the-audience-accept-ranbir-kapoor-as-ram-in-nitesh-tiwaris-upcoming-ramayana-asks-sunil-lahri%2Farticleshow%2F111081101.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22BPCL%20to%20invest%20Rs%201%2C400%20cr%20to%20set%20up%20sustainable%20aviation%20fuel%20facilities%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718699977000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2024-06%2F13%2Fthumb%2Ffeaturecrop%2F400X400%2F1718261734-9222.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fbpcl-to-invest-rs-1400-cr-to-set-up-sustainable-aviation-fuel-facilities-124061800430_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20company%20operates%20three%20refineries%20located%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20Kochi%2C%20and%20Bina%20(Madhya%20Pradesh)%2C%20with%20collectively%20refining%20capacity%20of%2035.3%20million%20metric%20tonnes%20per%20annum%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fbpcl-to-invest-rs-1400-cr-to-set-up-sustainable-aviation-fuel-facilities-124061800430_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fbpcl-to-invest-rs-1400-cr-to-set-up-sustainable-aviation-fuel-facilities-124061800430_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fbpcl-to-invest-rs-1400-cr-to-set-up-sustainable-aviation-fuel-facilities-124061800430_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22NDTV%20Most%20Popular%20For%20News%20In%20India%2C%20TV%20Or%20Digital%3A%20Reuters%20Institute%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EConsolidating%20its%20dominance%20in%20the%20news%20landscape%2C%20both%20online%20and%20offline%2C%20NDTV%20has%20emerged%20at%20the%20top%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Freutersinstitute.politics.ox.ac.uk%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2024-06%2FDNR%25202024%2520Final%2520lo-res-compressed.pdf%5C%22%3Esurvey%20by%20the%20prestigious%20Reuters%20Institute%20at%20Oxford%20University%3C%2Fa%3E.%20For%20the%20fourth%20time%20in%20a%20row%2C%20the%20survey%20has%20found%20that%20NDTV%2024X7%20is%20the%20country's%20most-watched%20news%20channel%20and%20ndtv.com%20the%20country's%20most%20popular%20news%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Reuters%20institute's%20Digital%20News%20Report%202024%2C%20NDTV%20accounts%20for%2033%20per%20cent%20of%20weekly%20use%20across%20the%20television%2C%20radio%20and%20print%20media.%20Likewise%2C%20ndtv.com%2C%20is%20ahead%20of%20the%20competition%20with%2027%20per%20cent%20weekly%20use%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Ffu621ado_reuters-institute-report_625x300_18_June_24.jpg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20the%20methodology%20used%20in%20the%20study%2C%20the%20Reuters%20Institute%20has%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThese%20data%20are%20based%20on%20a%20survey%20of%20mainly%20English-speaking%2C%20online%20news%20users%20in%20India%20-%20a%20small%20subset%20of%20a%20larger%2C%20more%20diverse%2C%20media%20market.%20Findings%20in%20this%20online%20poll%20are%20not%20nationally%20representative%20and%20will%20tend%20to%20under-represent%20the%20continued%20importance%20of%20traditional%20media%20such%20as%20TV%20and%20print.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2F3bdlc8t8_reuters-institute-report_625x300_18_June_24.jpg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20institute%20noted%20that%20its%20survey%20found%20that%20for%20a%20new%20generation%20of%20Indians%2C%20their%20main%20sources%20of%20news%20is%20often%20social%20media%20platforms.%20Almost%20half%20of%20respondents%20use%20YouTube%20(54%25)%20and%20WhatsApp%20(48%25)%20for%20news%20each%20week%2C%20while%20Facebook%20and%20X%20are%20becoming%20less%20popular%2C%20the%20study%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20added%2C%20platforms%20such%20as%20NDTV%20continue%20to%20enjoy%20high%20viewership%20in%20their%20offline%20and%20online%20products%2C%20among%20a%20younger%2C%20urban%2C%20mostly%20English-speaking%20sample.%20%26quot%3BDespite%20a%20general%20decline%20in%C2%A0interest%20in%20news%20over%20the%20years%2C%20print%20(40%25)%20and%20TV%20(46%25)%20remain%20popular%20platforms%20for%20respondents%20to%20access%20news%2C%20especially%20during%20this%20crucial%20election%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20survey%20also%20found%20that%20Indian%20readers%20have%20high%20trust%20in%20the%20NDTV%20brand%20as%20a%20source%20for%20news.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20underlined%20that%20partisan%20commercial%20broadcasters%20and%20independent%20digital%20portals%20%26quot%3Bwho%20are%20either%20uncritical%20or%20extremely%20critical%20of%20those%20in%20positions%20of%20power%20are%20actively%20distrusted%20by%20the%20respondents%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20thank%20you%20for%20trusting%20us%20and%20relying%20on%20us%20for%20the%20fastest%20and%20most%20credible%20news%20coverage.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718699820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F9holpgiao7_ndtv-mics-camera_625x300.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fndtv-tops-reuters-institute-survey-on-india-news-sources-4th-time-in-row-5914759%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Consolidating%20its%20dominance%20in%20the%20news%20landscape%2C%20both%20online%20and%20offline%2C%20NDTV%20has%20emerged%20at%20the%20top%20in%20a%20survey%20by%20the%20prestigious%20Reuters%20Institute%20at%20Oxford%20University.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fndtv-tops-reuters-institute-survey-on-india-news-sour