om%2F6670ecc3ed9a404d829e8fcf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223280%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChina's%20Dongfeng-41%20nuclear%20missiles%20on%20display%20during%20a%20military%20parade%20on%20October%201%2C%202019.%3Cp%3EXia%20Yifang%2FXinhua%20News%20Agency%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EChina%20increased%20its%20nuclear%20warheads%20from%20410%20in%202023%20to%20500%20this%20year%2C%20per%C2%A0SIPRI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20European%20think%20tank%20says%20China's%20nuclear%20arsenal%20is%20growing%C2%A0%26quot%3Bfaster%20than%20any%20other%20country.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EChina%20could%20have%20over%201%2C000%20operational%20nuclear%20warheads%20by%202030%2C%20per%20the%20Pentagon.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fxi-says-us-trying-trick-china-invade-taiwan-wont-succeed-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChina%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20beaten%20its%20fellow%20superpowers%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20growing%20its%20stockpile%20of%20nuclear%20warheads%2C%20a%20European%20think%20tank%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sipri.org%2Fmedia%2Fpress-release%2F2024%2Frole-nuclear-weapons-grows-geopolitical-relations-deteriorate-new-sipri-yearbook-out-now%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChina%20is%20expanding%20its%20nuclear%20arsenal%20faster%20than%20any%20other%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Hans%20M%20Kristensen%2C%20a%20Stockholm%20International%20Peace%20Research%20Institute%20(SIPRI)%20expert%20on%20weapons%20of%20mass%20destruction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20SIPRI%2C%20China%20has%20increased%20its%20nuclear%20warheads%20from%20410%20in%202023%20to%20500%20at%20the%20start%20of%20this%20year.%20But%20China%2C%20Kristensen%20said%2C%20isn't%20the%20only%20country%20that's%20been%20busy%20expanding%20its%20nuclear%20arsenal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENorth%20Korea%20has%20increased%20its%20warheads%20by%20two-thirds%20over%20the%20past%20year%2C%20going%20from%2030%20in%202023%20to%2050%20this%20year%2C%20per%20the%20think%20tank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20China's%20and%20North%20Korea's%20growing%20nuclear%20stockpiles%20still%20cannot%20compare%20to%20what%20the%20US%20and%20Russia%20have.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20total%20inventory%2C%20the%20US%20has%205%2C044%20warheads%20while%20Russia%20has%205%2C580%2C%20and%20their%20combined%20stockpile%20makes%20up%20almost%2090%25%20of%20the%20world's%20nuclear%20weapons%2C%20per%20SIPRI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20China's%20foreign%20ministry%20didn't%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20BI%20sent%20outside%20regular%20business%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a026f2bb-b770-4561-a8a9-871bcc44d199%5C%22%3EChina%20could%20have%20over%201%2C000%20warheads%20by%202030%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20institute's%20figures%20are%20in%20line%20with%20the%20Department%20of%20Defense's%20forecasts%2C%20which%20were%20published%20in%20October%20in%20their%20annual%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedia.defense.gov%2F2023%2FOct%2F19%2F2003323409%2F-1%2F-1%2F1%2F2023-MILITARY-AND-SECURITY-DEVELOPMENTS-INVOLVING-THE-PEOPLES-REPUBLIC-OF-CHINA.PDF%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChina%20Military%20Power%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%202020%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Defense%20estimated%20China's%20operational%20nuclear%20warhead%20stockpile%20was%20in%20the%20low-200s%20and%20expected%20to%20at%20least%20double%20by%202030%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20Beijing%20has%20accelerated%20its%20nuclear%20expansion%2C%20and%20the%20Department%20of%20Defense%20estimates%20China's%20stockpile%20had%20more%20than%20500%20operational%20nuclear%20warheads%20as%20of%20May%202023%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20China's%20nuclear%20stockpile%20will%20only%20continue%20to%20grow%20in%20the%20years%20to%20come.%20The%20Pentagon%20said%20in%20its%20report%20that%20it%20expects%20China%20to%20have%20over%201%2C000%20operational%20nuclear%20warheads%20by%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20changes%20to%20the%20numbers%2C%20capability%2C%20and%20readiness%20of%20the%20PRC's%20nuclear%20forces%20in%20the%20coming%20years%20are%20likely%20to%20outpace%20potential%20developments%20by%20the%20nuclear%20forces%20of%20any%20competitor%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said%20of%20China's%20growing%20nuclear%20capabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExpanding%20its%20nuclear%20arsenal%20isn't%20China's%20only%20military%20goal.%20The%20country%20has%20also%20been%20focused%20on%20bolstering%20its%20naval%20capabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%202021%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.usni.org%2F2021%2F11%2F03%2Fchina-has-worlds-largest-navy-with-355-ships-and-counting-says-pentagon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Navy%20Institute%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20China%20has%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-navy-destroyers-photos-fleet-list-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworld's%20largest%20navy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20over%20355%20vessels%20in%20its%20fleet.%20In%20July%2C%20leaked%20US%20Navy%20intelligence%20revealed%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-navy-chinas-shipbuilding-capacity-200-times-greater-than-us-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChina's%20shipbuilding%20capacity%20is%20232%20times%20greater%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20some%20military%20experts%20believe%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-not-ready-war-us-10-years-ex-nato-chief-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChina%20still%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20take%20on%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20next%20decade%2C%20even%20with%20its%20burgeoning%20military%20capabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChina%2C%20in%20my%20estimation%2C%20will%20not%20be%20ready%20to%20take%20on%20the%20US%20in%20a%20very%20mature%20way%20for%20about%2010%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20retired%20US%20Navy%20Adm.%20James%20Stavridis%20said%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmichaelmedved.com%2Fhighlight%2Fadmiral-stavridis-on-the-medved-show%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterview%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20%26quot%3BThe%20Michael%20Medved%20Show%26quot%3B%20in%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20though%20China%20is%20building%20a%20massive%20fleet%2C%20even%20though%20they're%20acting%20very%20aggressively%2C%20they're%20not%20ready%20yet%20to%20line%20up%20all%20that%20they%20need%20to%20take%20on%20the%20US%20Pacific%20Fleet%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-now-fastest-growing-nuclear-arsenal-in-the-world-report-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718683811000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6670ed56ed9a404d829e8fd9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-now-fastest-growing-nuclear-arsenal-in-the-world-report-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22China%20increased%20its%20nuclear%20warheads%20from%20410%20in%202023%20to%20500%20at%20the%20start%20of%202024%2C%20per%20the%20Stockholm%20International%20Peace%20Research%20Institute.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ktan%40businessinsider.com%20(Kwan%20Wei%20Kevin%20Tan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A85%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-now-fastest-growing-nuclear-arsenal-in-the-world-report-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Kohli%20ko%20flying%20kiss%3F'%3A%20Harshit%20on%20teasing%20batter.%20Watch%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718683442000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2